Fossils and fossilization, use of biological classification in fossil organisms, evolution of main faunal groups. Principles and methods of stratigraphy, stratigraphical units, correlation, biostratigraphy, geochronological scale.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Bases of palaeontology and stratigraphy.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course, a student is able to: * understand realtionships between living organisms and fossils; * understands basics of fossilization process and its outcomes; * has basic knowledge on morphology, distribution and geological application of the principal fossil groups; * is able to use more important stratigraphic terms and knows basics of stratigraphy; * understands basics of the biostratigraphical method and its application; * is able to use basic terminlogy of geochronology and understands basic architecture of the geochronological table.
